#CPEG 657 - Search & Data Mining ............. 2/15

###Special ROles of Textual Information
	* natural encoding
	* most common type of info
	* most basic form of info
	* most useful

###Text Management Applications
* Access - **Select** Information
* Mining - **Create** Knowledge
* Organization - **Add** Structure/Annotations

##Elements of Text info Management Technologies
>##Search (short-term)
>* Features
>	* Query refinement
>	* Universal Search
>	* Search Pad (Yahoo)
>
>##Mining
>* Database of Intentions
>	* Aggregate results of every search ever entered
>	* Aggregate results of every result
>	* ...
> 
>##Text Summarization
>* Motivation - Information overload
>	* 4 Billion URLs indexed by Google
>* Goal of text summarization
>	* 
>* Search Result Summarization (Google Results)
>
>##Information Filtering (long-term)
>* Stable & long term interest
>* Dynamif info source
>* System must make a delivery decision
>* Example - Google Alert, Spam Filter, Collaorative Filtering (Amazon)
>
>##Text Categorization
>* Supervised Learning Problem
>	* Given a set of pre-given labels, classify new documents
>* Email Spam Filters
>* Sentiment Analysis
>* Example Google News Categories
>
>##Clustering Problem
>* Discover "natural structure"
>* Group similar objects totgether
>* Exmple - Google News, Clusty
>
>##Information Extraction
>* Given raw text, identify things like date, location, start-end times, etc
>* Convert unstructured data to structured data
>
>##Information Visualization
>* Bring information to life
>* Given a set of text driving directions, display it graphically
>
>##Unsolved Problems
>* Socail Media
>* Big Data
>* 
